com.netflix.zeno.serializer
Class FrameworkDeserializer<D extends NFDeserializationRecord>

java.lang.Object
  com.netflix.zeno.serializer.FrameworkDeserializer<D>
Type Parameters:
D -
Direct Known Subclasses:
FastBlobFrameworkDeserializer, JsonFrameworkDeserializer
public abstract class FrameworkDeserializer<D extends NFDeserializationRecord>
extends java.lang.Object

Mirroring the FrameworkSerializer, FrameworkDeserializer will define the actions which must be taken to decode individual "Zeno native" elements during deserialization of objects. It will also define the method of traversal of serialized representations of Objects for deserialization via the specification of deserializeObject, deserializeList, deserializeSet, and deserializeMap methods.

There may or may not be a "deserialization", which corresponds to every "serialization". For example, one operation which ships with the zeno framework is a calculation of a hash of a given Object (see HashSerializationFramework). This is a one-way operation and therefore has no corresponding "deserialization". In this case, the HashFrameworkSerializer does not have a corresponding deserializer.
